@criccomini Haven't had a chance at work to work on this much--but the integration is fine, save for it not passing the integration tests.

Oddly, I've replicated the CI LDAP setup to a T on my local system, and it still doesn't pass there. I'm not sure what is causing it to fail. I've even rebased to master w/o any modifications, and it still does not pass on my local system.

¯_(ツ)_/¯

@bolkedebruin @mistercrunch any ideas?

@mistercrunch re: config

> Seems like this change could affect people by requiring new conf settings, is that what we want or should we just assume that everyone has all rights if those conf settings don't exist.

The current change shouldn't require any config settings. If you don't do anything, the code defaults to super user. If, however, you DO configure Airflow to have a superuser_filter/data_profiler_filter filters, then it will enforce them.
